The paper focuses on robotic manipulation, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep visual representations for rope manipulation suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely category. The paper also discusses learning policies and point-pair correspondences, indicating machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as possible categories. Finally, the use of a robot in the experiments suggests systems and control (cs.SY) as a potential category.
